                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The kurobozu is adjacent to a living creature that is paralyzed, slowed, stunned, or unconscious;</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The kurobozu leans over and sucks the breath from the target, who must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"22\" data-pf2-traits=\"incapacitation,necromancy,occult\" data-pf2-label=\"Steal Breath DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude</span> save. Regardless of the result, the creature is exposed to black apoxia and its breath reeks of carrion for 1 minute.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature can’t speak for 1 minute.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Sickened]{Sickened 2} and can’t speak for 1 minute.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, plus the creature falls @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Unconscious]{Unconscious} and begins suffocating.</p>"
                },
